Locate an area that has full sunlight or at least 5 hours of direct sunlight. Your plants will grow better with a lot of sun and the sun will help keep the water clean. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/53/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/53/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Find a spot that is wide open and does not have trees. Trees will provide unwanted shade and you will have to continuously clean leaves and tree debris out of the garden. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Build or place your water garden on level ground. You can add hills and varying heights when you put the water garden together. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e0/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e0/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use an area that has convenient access to electrical connections and fresh water. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Choose a small water garden if you are not sure where to locate it. When it is small enough, it can be moved from site to site until you find the right place. Small water gardens are also good if you do not have a lot of space. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a large water garden if you want to have a lot of plants, fish or a fountain. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pick a container for your small water garden, such as a wooden barrel or tub. Line the barrel with plastic or the rotting wood may damage your plants. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you want  a large water garden, choose the appropriate lining. Your water garden liner can be concrete, brick, clay, plastic, butyl rubber or fiberglass – it depends on the type of weather you get and which you prefer. Liners can be either rigid or flexible. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Water-Garden-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
